text: Gimel is the third letter of the Hebrew alphabet. The Phoenician letter gave rise to the Greek gamma (Γ), the Latin C, G and F, and the Cyrillic Г. In set theory (particularly in the theory of infinite cardinal numbers), the \gimel symbol is used to represent the gimel function. The Hebrew gimel corresponds to the letter G in English. == Related pages == * Hebrew numerals == References == Category:Hebrew alphabet
